                        <hr /><p><br />
	Foggy Bottom Campus combines the academic and residential amenities of a top notch university with the excitement and convenience of living in the heart of the city. From lecture halls to high tech labs, and small group meeting rooms to <a href="https://library.gwu.edu/about/facilities/study-spaces" target="_blank">open study spaces</a>, you&rsquo;ll find a wide range of learning environments to fit your needs and aspirations.</p><p>You&rsquo;ll also enjoy the culinary benefits of city life with a variety of <a href="https://dining.gwu.edu" target="_blank">dining and grocery</a> partners on and near campus. Explore the world through your tastebuds with restaurant offerings from different ethnic traditions or go on a food excursion to check out restaurants in D.C.&rsquo;s vibrant neighborhoods.</p><p>Walk to a variety of museums, parks and attractions or hop on the Metro, a bus or bike share for adventures all over the city. And your city experiences don&rsquo;t need to be confined to daylight hours, as many students enjoy &ldquo;midnight monumenting&rdquo; after the tourists have turned in for the night.</p><hr /><h2><span id="docs-internal-guid-80c4ea4b-e746-3e95-b6e0-313b5e421ec1">Everything Here is Within Reach, Come See for Yourself</span></h2><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-4 pos-one"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="10-minute bike ride to class at the National Gallery of Art" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/BikeRideNationalGallery_FoggyBottom_v3.png" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>&nbsp;</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div><div class="col-md-4 pos-two"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="8 Metro stops to your internship at the Capitol" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/MetroRideCapitol_FoggyBottom_v3.png" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>&nbsp;</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div><div class="col-md-4 pos-three"><article><p class="col-img"><img alt="Home to 3 campus libraries" class="img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/CampusLibraries_FoggyBottom.png" style="height:720px; width:1080px" /></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>&nbsp;</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div></div></div><ul class="justifyButtons"><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://undergraduate.admissions.gwu.edu/visit-gw" target="_blank">Schedule an Undergraduate Visit</a></span></li><li><span class="ghost-button reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://graduate.admissions.gwu.edu/campus-visits" target="_blank">Schedule a Graduate Visit</a></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="container"><div class="row test-l-f"><div class="col-md-12 doodad"><hr /></div></div><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><div class="test-l clearfix"><div class="test-img-left"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="Sebastian Vazquez" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/SebastianVazquezTestimonial_FoggyBottom_testimonials_LRW-0735.jpg" style="height:340px; width:443px" /></p></figure><div class="name-block light"><p class="name">Sebastian Vazquez</p><p class="affi">Class of 2019<br />
								Major: Undecided</p></div></div><div class="test-copy"><blockquote class="test-l-quote"><p class="quote"><span class="testimonial-light">&ldquo;</span><span class="testimonial-light"><span>The opportunities to do community service here are constant. I can easily get to anything with the Metro and in D.C. there are so many options. You have to be here for something you&#39;re passionate about and GW is the perfect place for me to do service and make something out of it.</span>&rdquo;</span></p></blockquote></div></div></article></div></div><div class="row test-l-u"><div class="col-md-12 doodad-not"><hr /></div></div></div><h2>Your Home in the City</h2><p>Just steps from the world&#39;s great institutions, your home&nbsp;on Foggy Bottom Campus will become your base for building friendships, advancing your studies and reflecting on your GW journey.</p><div class="theta_bloc"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 pos-one"><article><p class="col-img"></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p><strong><span class="reg-button lightblue">Living Space on Campus</span></strong></p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div></div></div><div id="theta_vid" style="max-width:80%;margin:auto;"><blockquote class="ricoh-theta-spherical-image" data-height="400" data-width="100%">District House Affinity Housing - <a href="https://theta360.com/s/sSnOOZzg4gQwZjGj22W2Y4m7E" target="_blank">Spherical Image - RICOH THETA</a></blockquote></div><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 pos-one"><article><p class="col-img"></p><header class="col-h"><h3 class="promo-title"></h3></header><section class="col-copy"><p>Explore a 360-degree view of an apartment-style room in the Dakota, one of our residence halls for upperclassmen on Foggy Bottom.&nbsp;</p></section><footer class="call-to-action"><p>&nbsp;</p></footer></article></div></div></div><div style="max-width:80%;margin:auto;"><blockquote class="ricoh-theta-spherical-image" data-height="300" data-width="100%">&nbsp;</blockquote></div></div><p class="rtecenter"><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="/campus-life">Learn More About Living&nbsp;on Campus</a></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="rai-one"><h2>Getting to Foggy Bottom<a id="foggy-bottom-directions" name="foggy-bottom-directions"></a></h2></header><div class="rai-no"><div class="rai-img-c rai-two"><div class="embed-container"><div class="embed-container"><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3105.0493366615856!2d-77.04934318381969!3d38.89998707957035!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89b7b7b0f1074fe5%3A0xd7302beaa4e61dfb!2s800+21st+St+NW%2C+Washington%2C+DC+20052!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1471873280156" style="border:0"></iframe></div></div></div><div class="rai-copy rai-three"><p>Foggy Bottom is conveniently located in the heart of Washington, D.C., close to three major airports, including Ronald Reagan Washington National, Washington Dulles International and Baltimore Washington International, as well as to Union Station where you can take the bus or train. Public transportation is at your doorstep with the Foggy Bottom/GWU Metro stop on the Orange, Blue&nbsp;and Silver lines located right on campus.</p><h3>Parking</h3><p>If you&#39;re driving to campus, you can enter the Marvin Center&#39;s address of 800 21st Street NW into your GPS as a reference point or head right to one of our <a href="http://virtualtour.gwu.edu/#!UMAP_2013090592962%7B%22layers%22%3A%5B%22ULAY_2013091338292%22%5D%7D" target="_blank">visitor parking garages</a>. Be sure to review the <a href="https://transportation.gwu.edu/visitors" target="_blank">parking garage rates and hours</a> before you arrive.</p><h3>Where to Stay</h3><p>There are a variety of hotels convenient to our Foggy Bottom. To find a hotel for your stay:</p><ul><li>Make a discounted reservation at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.campustravel.com/university/gwu/" target="_blank">one of our preferred hotels&nbsp;</a>and proceeds from your booking will go to the university</li><li><a href="https://procurement.gwu.edu/discounted-lodging-foggy-bottommount-vernon-campuses-0" target="_blank">Choose a hotel</a>&nbsp;that offers&nbsp;seasonal discount&nbsp;rates to the GW community</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul class="stackedButtons"><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/downloads/FoggyBottomCampusMap_ADM-1617-1_UpdatedJuly2016.pdf" target="_blank">Foggy Bottom Campus Map (PDF)</a></span></li><li><span class="ghost-button reg-button lightblue"><a href="http://virtualtour.gwu.edu/#!UMAP_2013090592962" target="_blank">Virtual Tour of Foggy Bottom Campus</a></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div></article></div></div></div><hr /><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-md-12"><article><header class="lai-one"><h2>Shuttle Service to Other Campuses</h2></header><div class="lai-no"><div class="lai-img-c lai-two"><figure><p class="i-wrap"><img alt="Students waiting for the shuttle outside of Funger Hall" class="t-img-responsive" src="https://www.gwu.edu/sites/www.gwu.edu/files/image/ShuttleFunger_FoggyBottom_Shuttles_UP_WLA_2013-3341.jpg" /></p><figcaption class="t-img-caption"><p>&nbsp;</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="lai-copy lai-three"><p>Use our campus shuttle services to easily head to <a href="/mount-vernon-campus">Mount Vernon Campus</a> or <a href="/virginia-science-technology-campus">Virginia Science and Technology Campus</a>&nbsp;(VSTC).</p><p>Ride the Vern Express shuttle for approximately 15 minutes to go to Mount Vernon Campus and enjoy a view of the Potomac River along the way.</p><p>Travel to Ashburn, VA, to visit VSTC on our:</p><ul><li>VSTC shuttle, which goes directly between Foggy Bottom Campus and VSTC</li><li>Wiehle Express shuttle, which goes to the Wiehle-Reston East Metro stop on the Silver Line, the closest stop to the campus</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul class="stackedButtons"><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://transportation.gwu.edu/mount-vernon-shuttle-vern-express" target="_blank">Mount Vernon Campus Shuttle Schedule</a></span></li><li><span class="reg-button lightblue"><a href="https://transportation.gwu.edu/virginia-campus-shuttles" target="_blank">Virginia Science &amp; Technology Campus Shuttle Schedule</a></span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><footer class="call-to-action">&nbsp;</footer></div></div></article></div></div></div>
